 collecting of Jewish art became a legitimate and even passionate pursuit, and signaled the entry of Jews into the art world as painters, collectors, and dealers.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt and society. 0aJewish art and symbolism. 0aJews in art. 0aJewsxIdentity. 0aJewsxIntellectual life. 4aArt. 4aEuropean. 7aART / European.2bisacsh1 aCohen, Richard I., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052020545140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091791040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520917910423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520917910/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles